<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-10T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="781" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/11–1044: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-10T19:00:00+03:00">November 10, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 11:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4313. ReDept’s 2487, October 20, 10 p.m. On October 25 I wrote to
                                Vyshinski to inform him concerning the public announcement made by
                                the Treasury and War Departments respecting the Allied military
                                mark. I also repeated the request originally made in Ambassador
                                Harriman’s letter of September 11 to Molotov for information on
                                Soviet plans for the use of military currency in Germany. As yet I
                                have had no reply.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>